‚ùìDo you feel like you often play a role or are you able to be your real self always?
‚Ä¢
I‚Äôm talking about a role which you create to pretend to be different than who you really are. Maybe because you are scared that you will not be accepted or you want to protect yourself, or gain validation and envy.
‚Ä¢
I think I am a little bit of both. It is probably impossible to be outwardly authentic 100% of the time. Life is a dance of duality: light/dark, pleasant/unpleasant, work/play, think/feel, truth/lies. Some situations in life really require us to wear a mask. With some people (not the closest ones), I have to play a role as well, but I have been feeling more and more myself in the last years. Living life scared to be yourself is not a healthy way of living.
‚Ä¢
‚ÄúBe yourself; everyone else is already taken.‚Äù-Oscar Wilde‚ù§Ô∏è
